dct_title_s: Map to accompany the notes on Manchuria
dct_description_sm: Relief shown by hachures and spot heights. "Highways traversed by Williamson, inns along them, and other highways are shown". Major areas of crop, mineral, and textile production are shown. Great Wall of China and palisade are shown. From: Journal of the Royal Geographical Society of London. Vol. 39 (1869), pp. 1-36; held in Firestone Library. Call number: G7 .J687
dct_publisher_sm: London : published for the Journal of the Royal Geographical Society by John Murray, Albemarle St., 1870.
London, 6 & 7 Charing Cross. : Stanford's Geogl. Estabt., [1870].
